96431.name: Under five mortality rate (per 1000 live births) (Gapminder and UN Population Division)
96431.description: The probability that a child born in a specific year will die before reaching the age of five if subject to current age-specific mortality rates. Expressed as a rate per 1,000 live births.
96431.datasetName: Under five mortality rate - Gapminder and UN Population Division (2017)
96431.s_name: Gapminder estimates up until 1949 and UN Population Division from 1950 to today
